secondary_street_name: bounded by Dalston Lane, Roseberry Place, Forest Road
description: Redevelopment of the site through the erection of part 7, part 10 and part 18/19 storey mixed use development comprising 309 residential units (78 x 1 bed, 135 x 2 bed and 96 x 3 bed), 1100 sqm of class A1 (Retail) floor space, 200 sqm of Class A3 (Food and Drink) floor space, 200 sqm of A4 (Drinking Establishments) floor space and 180 sqm of D1 (Non-residential institutions) floor space, 35 disabled car parking space, pedestrian entrances to the new East London Line Station and provision of a new ground floor level bus interchange facility. Replacement of Forest Road Bridge and demolition of 570 - 572 Kingsland Road, 1 - 3 Roseberry Place and 2 - 2a Dalston Lane.
